        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Q7: Are the provisions of the Proposed Law adequate to ensure effective conduct of an arbitration? If not what are the deficiencies, and how should they be addressed? ",
        "bbox": [
            57,
            323,
            948,
            370
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Q8: Given the central role of the Court in the administration of trusts, is the proposed structure of a right to arbitration where the trust instrument so provides, coupled with a discretionary power on the part of the Court to refer other matters appropriate? If not, how should the balance be struck? ",
        "bbox": [
            53,
            491,
            953,
            557
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
